
## Deep isolation findings (2026-07-24)
- STATIC mask geometry is CORRECT: with offset=in (write-on off) + frozen position/scale, FCP and
  engine both ~26% coverage, similar bbox. So parse/rasterize/feather/scale of a single static quad
  is fine. The bug is NOT static geometry.
- The divergence is ENTIRELY the WRITE-ON sweep. Engine coverage caps ~71-85% and HOLDS; FCP reaches
  100% by scene t~0.65 then conceals L->R at the very end (t>0.95).
- The mask legitimately animates Position (X -1045.8->2105.2, Y -2129->1870 over local 0.30->1.07)
  AND Scale (X const 2.088; Y 0.686->5.941 over local -0.20->0.57). Both are sampled by the write-on.
- The offset re-anchor (curveTime = timeSec - offset(0.30)) is NOT the cause: disabling it
  (FCT_NO_REANCHOR probe) leaves coverage at 71%.
- Write-on sub-time dump at t=0.70 (curveTime=0.494): the 13 swept quads run pos (-367,-1183)->(843,210),
  scale.Y 1.82->4.81. Early quads sit ABOVE the frame (Y=-1183, frame top -540); only late quads enter.
  The union traces a diagonal band that misses the frame's TOP-RIGHT and BOTTOM-LEFT corners.
- OPEN QUESTION for next iteration: why does FCP's swept mask reach 100% when the quad-union caps at
  ~71-85%? Hypotheses to test: (a) FCP's Scale.Y (up to 5.94) makes the quad tall enough to cover the
  full column at each X — check if the engine is applying the FULL scale.Y at the correct sub-times or
  clamping it; (b) the Scale curve local times [-0.20,0.57] vs Position [0.30,1.07] are on DIFFERENT
  anchors — the engine samples both at the same `st`, but FCP may co-evaluate them at a consistent
  scene time, so the engine's quad is smaller-than-FCP at the sweep positions where it matters;
  (c) FCP's reveal may be a continuous swept-region (not K=12 discrete quads) — increase K and/or
  rasterize the swept HULL between consecutive sub-quads to fill gaps.
- NEXT CONCRETE STEP: freeze Position to a static mid-frame value but KEEP Scale animating (and vice
  versa) to determine whether the coverage shortfall is driven by the Position sweep or the Scale ramp.

## ROOT CAUSE FOUND (2026-07-24) — anchor point is scaled, shifting the mask off-frame
Instrumented the mask's world transform (FCT_MTX_DEBUG) on the max-scale-static-centered repro:
  worldTransform: sx=1.846 (=2.088 mask × 0.884 parent ✓), sy=5.253, tx=1141, ty=1275 (!!)
The SCALE is correct, but the TRANSLATION is +1141,+1275 — WAY off the bottom-right of the 1920×1080
frame — even though the mask Position is (0,0). Source: the mask has Anchor Point Y=-238.4, and
buildTransformMatrix composes M = T(pos)·R·S·T(-anchor), i.e. screen = pos + S·(v - anchor). With
scaleY=5.253 and anchorY=-238, the anchor offset is SCALED: 238×5.253 ≈ 1250 = the ty shift. So the
whole mask is pushed off-frame, covering only 55% (static) / 71% (swept) instead of FCP's 94-100%.
CONTROL: FCP with anchorY=-238 → 94% coverage; anchorY=0 → 100%. So FCP applies the anchor but its
effect is SMALL (a slight shift), NOT the massive scaled shift the engine produces. => FCP does NOT
scale the anchor offset the way the engine does (or pivots scale around the anchor so the anchor
point stays fixed). This is the ROOT CAUSE of the Wipes__Diagonal mask-coverage divergence.

FIX DIRECTION (careful — buildTransformMatrix is shared by ALL 65 transitions; must not regress):
the anchor-point/scale composition needs to match Motion's convention. Candidates to test:
  (a) pivot-around-anchor: screen = pos + anchor + R·S·(v - anchor)  [anchor added back so the
      anchor point maps to pos+anchor, not scaled away] — verify against a layer that uses BOTH a
      non-zero anchor and scale (this mask) AND ones that currently pass (Fall anchor -540, Reflection
      anchor Z=960) so no regression.
  (b) anchor is a pure rotation pivot (not scaled/translated for scale) — Motion's "Anchor Point"
      may only pivot rotation, with scale about the layer origin.
  NEXT: read Motion's actual transform order (ENGINE_RE_PLAYBOOK / OZTransformNode) or empirically
  fit by rendering FCP with a few (anchor, scale) combos and matching the engine. Then implement +
  verify: this repro reaches ~99 dB, golden test:node green, min-regress no worse, full 65 re-scored.
